-garde theater, and conceptual art and demonstrates not only the emergence of poet's theater in the postwar period but its continuation and legacy today.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aPerformance poetry. 0aTheaterzUnited Statesy20th centuryxHistory. 0aAmerican dramay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan),eissuing body.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9373485